The scenes of the musial Find New Roads. Photo: Courtesy to the Find New Roads.  The original musical Find New Roads debuted at Beijing Tianqiao Performing Arts Center on October 2. As one of the first plays to be premiered after the ceiling of the theater audience was adjusted to 75 percent, the tickets of the musical were sold out before the show started. The musical, produced by car company Chevy, gathers the main creators behind the new concept performance work Apologue 2047. The new work tells the encouraging story of ordinary people in a large metropolis striving toward their dreams and looking for meaning in their lives. The show includes 24 original music pieces that resonate with the story’s plots. 

The scenes of the musial Find New Roads. Photo: Courtesy to the Find New Roads.  After Beijing, the show will tour to six other cities in China, including Shenzhen in South China’s Guangdong Province, Qingdao in East China’s Shandong Province and Chengdu, capital of Southwest China’s Sichuan Province. Massive changes to California voting spark fears of Iowa-style primary chaosAsian Americans wait for their turn to shine in HollywoodCal's epidemic protection services still have room for improvement